\begin{align*}
x+y&=3\\
2x+y&=2
\end{align*}

Subtracting the second equation from the first, we get

\begin{align*}
x-2x&=3-2\\
-x&=1\\
x&=-1
\end{align*}

Substituting $x=-1$ into the first equation, we find

